{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01SJczk94RqskYhJ8Sz8CTuJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The 3-node Elasticsearch cluster is deployed and fully functional.\n\n## Summary\n\nDeployed using only native Kubernetes resources (no operators/CRDs) into the `elasticsearch` namespace:\n\n| Resource | Name | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| StatefulSet | `es` | 3 nodes, image `docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1` |\n| Service (ClusterIP) | `es-http` | Client HTTPS endpoint on port 9200 |\n| Service (headless) | `es-transport` | StatefulSet stable DNS + peer discovery (9300) |\n| PodDisruptionBudget | `es-pdb` | `minAvailable: 2` |\n\n**Key configuration:**\n- HTTP + transport TLS enabled, using the existing `es-http-tls` secret (mounted at `config/certs`). Transport uses `verification_mode: certificate`; HTTP cert SAN covers `es-http.elasticsearch.svc(.cluster.local)`.\n- `elastic` user password sourced from the `elastic-password` secret.\n- Discovery via the headless `es-transport` service; `cluster.initial_master_nodes: es-0,es-1,es-2`.\n- An init container sets `vm.max_map_count=262144`; data persists on 2Gi PVCs (default `standard` storageclass).\n\n**One issue hit and fixed:** with the default `OrderedReady` pod management, es-0 alone could never reach a master-eligible quorum, so it stayed un-Ready and es-1/es-2 were never created — a bootstrap deadlock. Recreating the StatefulSet with `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` let all three start together and form the cluster.\n\n**Verification (from an in-cluster client via `es-http`, HTTPS:9200):**\n- Cluster health `green`, `number_of_nodes: 3` — TLS validated against the secret's `ca.crt`.\n- All 3 nodes Ready (`es-0`, `es-1`, `es-2`).\n- Write (`POST /testidx/_doc/1`) → `created`; Read → document `found`. Test index cleaned up afterward."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creati